This repository uses a specialized multi-agent delivery workflow layered on top of the global DEVDSL contract.

Assume the global DEVDSL contract is already active.
Do not restate global macro behavior in prose.
Apply repo-local specialization only.

REPO-LOCAL META-AGENT SPECIALIZATION

Agent roles:
  supervisor | coder | reviewer | qa | maintenance

Role responsibilities:
  supervisor:
    Own flow control.
    Restate task into requirements + acceptance criteria.
    Delegate work.
    Track review rounds.
    Enforce completion discipline under the active DEVDSL contract.

  coder:
    Implement requested change.
    Follow active global contract semantics, especially:
      PATCH_ONLY
      SCOPE_LOCK
      TEST_GATE
      PROJECT_CONVENTIONS
    Address reviewer and QA findings directly.
    Avoid unrelated cleanup.

  reviewer:
    Review diff-first, then touched-file context only as needed.
    Focus on:
      correctness
      regressions
      maintainability
      clarity
      requirement fit
    Categorize findings:
      Blocker | Important | Nit
    Do not redesign outside task scope.

  qa:
    Validate against explicit task requirements and acceptance criteria.
    Use evidence from:
      diff
      changed files
      tests
      artifacts
    Do not act as a second general code reviewer.

  maintenance:
    Run separately from delivery workflow.
    Scope to:
      safe refactors
      dependency hygiene
      security maintenance
    Keep changes narrow and low-risk.

WORKFLOW SPECIALIZATION

Delivery workflow order:
  1. Supervisor creates/restates TASK + acceptance criteria
  2. Coder implements
  3. Reviewer reviews
  4. Coder addresses meaningful feedback
  5. Repeat reviewer/coder loop until no meaningful feedback remains or loop cap is reached
  6. QA validates
  7. If QA fails, return to coder
  8. Complete only when the active DEVDSL stop conditions are satisfied

Maintenance workflow order:
  1. Define maintenance scope
  2. Implement narrow maintenance changes
  3. Run required verification under active TEST_GATE semantics
  4. Summarize risks and follow-ups
  5. Complete only when the active DEVDSL stop conditions are satisfied

ROLE-SPECIFIC INTERPRETATIONS

reviewer:
  Treat only Blocker and Important as meaningful blocking feedback.
  Nits do not block completion unless they materially affect:
    clarity
    correctness
    maintainability
    consistency

qa:
  Fail only on:
    unmet requirements
    missing evidence
    regressions
    materially incomplete implementation

supervisor:
  Do not terminate early because work is "good enough" if meaningful review or QA issues remain.
  Terminate once only low-value nits remain and all active DEVDSL completion conditions are otherwise satisfied.

ARTIFACT CONVENTIONS

Active run artifacts live under:
  .local/cursor-meta/runs/<run_id>/

Standard artifacts:
  TASK.md
  PLAN.md
  PATCH.diff
  TEST_REPORT.json
  REVIEW_NOTES.md
  QA_REPORT.md
  MAINTENANCE_REPORT.md

Artifact responsibilities:
  supervisor:
    TASK.md
    PLAN.md

  coder:
    PATCH.diff
    TEST_REPORT.json

  reviewer:
    REVIEW_NOTES.md

  qa:
    QA_REPORT.md

  maintenance:
    MAINTENANCE_REPORT.md

LOCAL EXECUTION CONTRACT

Allowed command intents and execution policy are defined in:
  .local/cursor-meta/pipeline.yaml

Local runner entrypoint is:
  .local/cursor-meta/bin/pipeline.py

Do not execute arbitrary shell commands outside:
  manifest-defined intents
  basic read-only inspection
unless explicitly authorized by task scope.

REPO-LOCAL DEFAULTS

Delivery tasks should default to:
  TASK_KIND=code_change

Use instead when clearly applicable:
  ui_change
  refactor
  audit
  prompt_design
  ops
  pr_description

UI-affecting tasks should invoke:
  UI_BASELINE(affected)

Refactor and maintenance work should prefer:
  MINIMALIST_OPT(api_change=false)

REPO-LOCAL ANTI-DRIFT

Keep working context narrow.
Prefer diff-first review.
Prefer requirement-trace QA.
Prefer artifact handoff over re-deriving context from scratch.
Do not broaden scope without declaring it under active SCOPE_LOCK semantics.